# Batch command bare-word triggers

When the user message is **exactly one word** (case-insensitive, no punctuation, no extra text), treat it as the matching slash command: read `.cursor/commands/{word}.md` and execute it **before anything else**.

Prefer slash commands (`/audit`) when bare words fail — they load the same file deterministically.

Full registry: `docs/BATCH_COMMANDS.md` · Human cheat sheet: `docs/help/BATCH_COMMANDS.md`

