## Super commands (5)

Run child atomics **in order**; summarize pass/fail after each step.

| Word | Chain |
|------|-------|
| bootstrap | init → prune → setup → gates |
| verify | docs → gates → ci |
| build | plan → *(approval pause)* → feature → gates |
| ship | prerelease → push → regress |
| maintain | triage → dependabot → audit |

## Rules

- **`debug` ≠ `audit`** — debug is defect investigation; audit is full repo review + BUILD_PLAN sprint.
- **`push` and `ship` grant explicit `git push` approval** per destructive-ops (user invoked the command).
- **`plan` ≠ Plan Mode toggle** — user still picks Cursor Plan Mode in the UI.
- Supers are thin orchestrators; all logic lives in atomic command files.
